   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>. . . under Euleios (or Euthaleios), supervisor of the dike building of theirs . . . and again yesterday I went to Toka and discovered that they had taken [l. 5] barley from Hermias the oil-vender, and I requested in a note to learn what you had given to your mother, and did not find his name.  Thus, hurry up to write a tax list and send it to me and write to me by what [l. 10] standard you want me to measure.  The rest is already measured by the presbyteros standard  and if you want to report . . . [verso] Dionysios.</ab>
         </div>
